			%br
			<span class="example">ijcomm:<i>commname</i></span>
			%br
	%div{ :class => "span-8 last" }
		%h3
			Category tags
		%div.span-4
			- @order.each do |tag|
				#{@categories[tag]}
				%br
		%div{:class =>"span-4 last"}
			- @order.each do |tag|
				<span class="example">cat:#{tag}</span>
				%br
	%div{ :class => "span-16 last", :style => "padding-top: 2em" }
		%h3
			Series tags
		%p
			Items in a series, such as a multi-chapter fic, can be connected into a single entry in the newsletter by a <span class="example">series:</span> tag. Invent a meaningful tag for each series. Use one word from the title or join multiple words together with hyphens. (Pinboard tags can't have spaces in them.) Examples:
		%p
			<span class="example">series:teatime</span>
			%br
			<span class="example">series:band-candy</span>
			%br
			<span class="example">series:giles-is-awesome</span>
			%br
		%p
			Create series pinboard bookmarks in the order you want them to appear in the newsletter. That is, if you want chapters 5, 6, and 7 of a series to appear in the newsletter, bookmark chapter 5 first, then chapter 6, and so on.
